'''Ksar Ouled Soltane''' ([[Wikipedia:Arabic language|Arabic]]: قصر أولاد سلطان) is a fortified granary, or ksar, located in southern [[Tunisia]]. The ksar is spread out over two courtyards, each of which has a perimeter of multi-story vaulted granary cellars, or [[Wikipedia:Ghorfas|ghorfas]]. Like other ksour created by North African [[Wikipedia:Berber people|Berber]] communities, Ksar Ouled Soltane is located on a hilltop, to help protect it from raiding parties in previous centuries.

Ksar Ouled Soltane is now a tourist destination, with visitors coming to see its well-preserved granary vaults. It is one of three [[Wikipedia:ksar|ksour]] around [[Wikipedia:Tataouine|Tataouine]] to represent the [[Slave Quarters Row/Legends|Slave Quarters Row]] of [[Mos Espa]] in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']], where [[Anakin Skywalker]] lived as a boy.

